"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"90d7d5",
"children":[
"Achalasia often presents with dysphagia for solids and liquids and regurgitation of undigested food."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_gi_s2_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"58f458",
"children":[
"Diagnostic evaluation should be performed in the following order:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"18c0ef",
"children":[
"barium esophagography; shows “bird's beak” narrowing of the ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"gastroesophageal",
"children":[
"GE"
]
},
" junction"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ac5139",
"children":[
"upper endoscopy to rule out adenocarcinoma (pseudoachalasia) at the GE junction"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"833567",
"children":[
"esophageal manometry confirms diagnosis by documenting absence of peristalsis and incomplete relaxation of the ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"lower esophageal sphincter",
"children":[
"LES"
]
},
" with swallows"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c38dc4",
"children":[
"If the patient has a history of travel to South America, suspect Chagas disease as the cause of achalasia."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
